    {
      "id": "18b5a48b9e8eff581a1308ec037a43c034dcd763",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-27 00:11:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nHow does this relate to http://review.whamcloud.com/8355 ?  It seems that this is more \"unified\" than the other patch, which is actually making the OST and MDT OUT handling separate, so this one seems better.\n\nThat said, why did you pick OSC_REPLY_PORTAL instead of MDC_REPLY_PORTAL?\n\nI'd definitely like feedback from Di on this, since he wrote the other patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "389edd8b68f392e28daf76b61bbee59dd9917139",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-27 07:02:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas, we've discussed that recently, osc_reply_portal is safer for interoperability as MDTs are easier to update at once. With mdc_reply_portal we would need to update both MDT and OST at the same time",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2c7599355210d1c0ce345201a327020bbd743d96",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-27 07:05:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis is patch is alternative to 8355 you mentioned.  I know about this problem with different reply portal and suppose Di encountered it. If so then this solution is preferable.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
